cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about language models and their ability to generate text with specific attributes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of classifiers and neural networks, which suggests that it could also fit into the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of gradients to guide text generation, which could fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper includes examples of image captioning, which could potentially place it in the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
